race.comment: PEARL ADIOS (2) is a track and distance winner from two starts ago that wasn't disgraced behind some handy horses over 1200m last start. He looks hard to beat back up to 1400m from a good draw with a 2kg claim. TOSEN WATER (7) drops in grade after tackling the Gawler Cup last start. A slight drop in distance might help her chances here and she can run in the money. ANGELIC APPEAL (13) is mixing her form but is capable of a cheeky run with no weight on her back, while JILLADORA (3) is a last-start winner that has great form at the track and distance. Don't leave her out. JILLADORA (3) bounced back to winning form at Penola last start and rates a chance in this field.
